[72.509512, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mI did not modify your script or machinery at all.\u001b[53G\u001b[22mThe\u001b[57Gspawn\u001b[63Gscript\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B(\u001b[38;5;153mspawn-branch.sh\u001b[39m)\u001b[21Gis\u001b[24Guntouched\u001b[34G—\u001b[36Git\u001b[39Gstages\u001b[46Gthe\u001b[50Gprompt\u001b[57Gthe\u001b[61Gsame\u001b[66Gway\u001b[70Git\u001b[73Galways\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bhas: \u001b[38;5;153mtmux send-keys -l \"<topic text>\"\u001b[39m, literally typing the\u001b[63Gtop\u001b[67Gc into\u001b[74Gthe\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Binput box.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mWhat I broke: I passed a ~900-character topic string.\u001b[57G\u001b[22mClaude\u001b[64GCode's\u001b[71GTUI\u001b[75Ghas\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bpaste\u001b[9Gdetection\u001b[19G—\u001b[21Gwhen\u001b[26Gthat\u001b[31Gmany\u001b[36Gcharacters\u001b[47Garrive\u001b[54Gin\u001b[57Gone\u001b[61Gburst,\u001b[68Git\u001b[71Gdoesn't\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Brender them as typed text; it collapses them into a colore\u001b[62G \u001b[38;5;153m[Pasted text #1]\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[39mattachm\u001b[11Gnt chip. That's the\u001b[31Gpersistent colored blob you're seeing, and it\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bb\u001b[5Ghaves like an attachment\u001b[31Gnstead of typed tex\u001b[51G,\u001b[53Gwhich is why it lingers\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1Bf\u001b[6Ger Enter. Your previous dive\u001b[35G worked because the\u001b[55Gt\u001b[57Gpics\u001b[62Gw\u001b[64Gre short\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bone-liners —\u001b[16Gshor\u001b[21G enough that send-keys reads as\u001b[53Gnormal typing, exactly \"as\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bi\u001b[5G you typed\u001b[16Git out.\"\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B          \u001b[14G \u001b[16G     \u001b[22G     \u001b[55G\u001b[K\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
