[694.685042, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1m\"Layer 2\" becomes the second layer of the connection — a QUIC-native secure \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdata plane that the HTTP handshake upgrades into, not literal ethernet \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bbridging.\u001b[22m Concretely:\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mOne QUIC connection, two personalities.\u001b[45G\u001b[22mDevPulse\u001b[54Ghits\u001b[59Gthe\u001b[63GBrain\u001b[69GAPI\u001b[73Gover\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BHTTP/3\u001b[10G(\u001b[38;5;153mclyffy.local:8787\u001b[39m,\u001b[30GmDNS\u001b[35Gdiscovery\u001b[45G—\u001b[47Gunchanged\u001b[57Gcontract).\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BEnrollment/auth happens there, then the \u001b[3msame connection\u001b[59G\u001b[23mop\u001b[62Gns dedicated\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bstreams + unreliable datagrams as the fast path: rkyv\u001b[57Gzero-copy frames,\u001b[75Gno\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BJSON, no per-request over\u001b[30Gad.\u001b[34GT\u001b[36Gis\u001b[39Gis the literal \"goes from\u001b[65GHTTP to the\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bbridge immediately\" — no second handshake,\u001b[46Gno system VPN config, no admi\u001b[76G\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bprompts,\u001b[12Gidentical on Linux/Window\u001b[38G/Mac b\u001b[45Gcaus\u001b[50G it's all\u001b[60Gin-process Rust\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B(quinn/quiche + rustls).\u001b[28G\u001b[K\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;4H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
