[860.831394, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H  \u001b[38;5;153m\u001b[1mconnectome-protocol\u001b[39m surface\u001b[22m. I'm striking \"rkyv-framed\" from the proposal\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B  (that was me reaching for a shiny thing your stack already solves — good\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcatch).\u001b[11Grkyv\u001b[16Gstays\u001b[22Gout\u001b[26Gunless\u001b[33Ga\u001b[35Gmeasured\u001b[44GRust↔Rust\u001b[54Ghot\u001b[58Gpath\u001b[63Gsomeday\u001b[71Gproves\r\u001b[1B \u001b[3GFlatBuffers is the\u001b[22Glimiter,\u001b[33Gich I doubt.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2B \u001b[4Go the full decision now reads: \u001b[1mHTTP/3 handshake on the Brain API → same QUIC \r\u001b[1B\u001b[22m  \u001b[1mconnection upgrades in place to the fast path → FlatBuffers-framed \u001b[22m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mstreams/datagrams → edge termination at clyffy-01 (fabric sealed) → connection\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bmigration for weak links → hybrid PQ via rustls → hash-chained session ledger\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bin connectome → benchmark gate vs plain FlatBuffers-over-TCP, \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BNepTUN-embedded-WG as the held fallback.\r\u001b[2B\u001b[22m \u001b[3GConfirm and I'll write the DECISIONS.md + SUMMARY.md\u001b[56Gclose-out.\r\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246m✻\u001b[3GCooked for\u001b[14G1m 12s\r\u001b[4B\u001b[39m❯ \u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
